iewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://www.economist.com/graphic-detail/2024/01/12/eight-charts-illustrate-2023s-extreme-weather">经济学人</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>这并不意味着世界变暖已经超过 1.5°C——要正式跨过这个门槛，温度必须年复一年地保持在这个水平。如果运气好的话，气温会有所回升，2023 年将异常炎热。但每年气温上升的趋势是明确无误的，2023 年甚至帮助最坚定的怀疑者平息了。</p><p>当然，多年来，我们一直被告知气候变化最终将导致南极洲的冰层融化，从而导致世界各地的海平面上升。嗯，到目前为止，这种情况只发生了一点点。但南极洲<em>周围的</em>海冰在 2023 年融化到了前所未有的程度： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0df89303-8a76-433e-8b00-afa52a8ceb72_384x438.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0df89303-8a76-433e-8b00-afa52a8ceb72_384x438.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0df89303-8a76-433e-8b00-afa52a8ceb72_384x438.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0df89303-8a76-433e-8b00-afa52a8ceb72_384x438.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0df89303-8