欧亚大陆和非洲的人民正在一系列<a href="https://www.vox.com/world-politics/2024/1/25/24049551/war-increasing-ukraine-gaza-sudan-ethiopia">不断扩散的战争</a>中战斗并死亡。但即使世界变得更加黑暗，我<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-new-1970s">仍然感觉到</a>美国社会中的一些绿芽开始探出头来。 2010 年代的裂痕尚未得到弥合，但人们已开始尝试修复问题。</p><p>举一个小例子：去年，乡村音乐歌手 Luke Combs <a href="https://variety.com/2023/music/news/luke-combs-fast-car-hitmakers-tracy-chapman-crossover-1235813084/">翻唱了</a>Tracy Chapman 1988 年的歌曲“Fast Car”。一些作家和社交媒体的鼓吹者<a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/arts-entertainment/2023/07/13/tracy-chapman-luke-combs-fast-car-cover/">试图对库姆斯的封面提出质疑</a>。但查普曼近年来几乎从未在公开场合表演过，他特意从半退休状态中走出来，并在格莱美颁奖典礼上与库姆斯<a href="https://people.com/grammys-2024-tracy-chapman-fast-car-no-1-following-luke-combs-duet-8559354">合唱了</a>《Fast Car》。您可以<a href="https://www.grammy.com/videos/tracy-chapman-luke-combs-fast-car-2024-grammys-performance-66th-annual-grammy-awards">在此处观看表演视频</a>。这是一个很小的迹象，表明美国人可能开始抵制 2010 年代下意识的分裂思维。</p><p>无论如何，今天综述的主题是“社会治愈的小迹象”。但首先，播客！这是 Econ 102 的一集，由 Erik Torenberg 和特邀嘉宾 Eli Dourado 主持。 Eli 和我争论我们是否应该对科技的未来持乐观态度，结果证明我比他更乐观！ </p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8ac9ab643165b3c99e2b571a68&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;E29: Is the Great Stagnation Over?&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith, Erik Torenberg&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/4uAwVnTaSDixCEJqLay7HX&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;noScroll&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/4uAwVnTaSDixCEJqLay7HX" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p>这里是<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/no/podcast/econ-102-with-noah-smith-and-erik-torenberg/id1696419056">Apple 播客</a>和<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/no/podcast/econ-102-with-noah-smith-and-erik-torenberg/id1696419056">YouTube</a>链接。</p><p>我还出现在丹·舒尔茨的播客“Undertone”上。我们讨论了非常广泛的话题： </p><div id="youtube2-7wi1ZWbZBOc" class="youtube-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;7wi1ZWbZBOc&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:null,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}" data-component-name="Youtube2ToDOM"><div class="youtube-inner"><iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/7wi1ZWbZBOc?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" gesture="media" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowautoplay="true" allowfullscreen="true" width="728" height="409"></iframe></div></div><p>这里是<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/undertone/id1693303954?i=1000643514905">Apple 播客</a>和<a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/3gySmZWDXINAwJuraZM2Bg?si=077c34edf7954a92&amp;nd=1&amp;dlsi=8939b19e6c0a4fa0">Spotify</a>链接。</p><p>不管怎样，我们来看看本周有趣的事情清单：</p><h4> 1.让美国恢复正常</h4><p>乌克兰战争爆发后不久，我写了一篇关于美国左翼和右翼激进分子如何支持俄罗斯事业的文章，因为他们希望美国领导的世界秩序的不稳定能够帮助他们在美国境内获得权力： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;f20512ff-916a-413d-910c-b90c2f1252f9&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;In the first couple of weeks after Vladimir Putin ordered his legions into Ukraine, the media narrative was overwhelmed by the moral clarity of the situation. A totalitarian tyrant had launched a murderous, unprovoked invasion of another country, whose people were valiantly fighting to defend themselves. America&#8217;s hyper-partisan shouters, if not exactly&#8230;&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Putin's war and the Chaos Climbers&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2022-03-21T08:50:26.382Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.